  "text": "Microcin production and immunity or resistance assays. Microcin production was assayed by patch test, which consisted of picking each strain under study with a sterile toothpick and stabbing it onto a lawn of MccH47-sensitive cells (e.g., RYC1000). After incubation of the plates, halos of growth inhibition appeared around MccH47-producing stabs. Microcin immunity or resistance was evaluated by the cross-streaking method, and detection of intracellular MccH47 was performed by cell lysis [CITATION_1] . The antibiotic activity in the cell lysates was assayed on a lawn of microcin-sensitive cells.",
